в”Ӯ patch_type               в”Ӯ full                                                                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ patch_name               в”Ӯ hierarchical_entanglement_ansatz                                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ patch_description        в”Ӯ This redesign restructures the ansatz architecture to use a hierarchical entanglement     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ pattern with adaptive parameter sharing. Key improvements:                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 1. **Hierarchical Entanglement Layers**: Instead of applying all CZ gates uniformly, the  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ ansatz uses a multi-level entanglement strategy:                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ    - Layer 1: Entangle outer ring (corners and edges) with local rotations                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ    - Layer 2: Entangle center with edges using controlled rotations                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ    - Layer 3: Apply residual rotations with parameter sharing across symmetric positions  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 2. **Adaptive Parameter Sharing**: Parameters are shared across grid symmetries (4-fold   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ rotational symmetry of the tic-tac-toe board), reducing the parameter count from 162 to   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ ~54 per block while maintaining expressivity through strategic reuse.                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 3. **Modularized Gate Construction**: The ansatz specification is now built               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ programmatically with clear separation between:                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ    - Ring entanglement (outer 8 qubits)                                                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ    - Hub entanglement (center qubit 8 with edges)                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ    - Residual rotations with symmetry-aware sharing                                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 4. **Improved Data Flow**: The specification is generated once during validation rather   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ than hardcoded, making it easier to experiment with different entanglement patterns and   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ parameter sharing schemes.                                                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 5. **Reduced Overfitting**: The parameter sharing and hierarchical structure naturally    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ regularize the model, reducing the generalization gap while maintaining or improving test в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ accuracy through more efficient parameter utilization.                                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ This approach reduces parameters by ~67% while potentially improving accuracy through     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ better inductive bias aligned with the tic-tac-toe board's symmetry structure.            в”Ӯ
