в”Ӯ patch_description        в”Ӯ Inspired by the patterns in the prior seeds, this proposal builds a symmetry-aware        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ hierarchical ansatz with explicit parameter sharing by board class (corner, edge,         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ center). It preserves the fixed data map, uploading structure, and measurement scheme,    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ but replaces ANSATZ_SPEC with a more expressive yet compact layout:                       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Layer 1: Pre-entanglement RZ gates grouped by corner/edge/center with shared parameters в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ across symmetric qubits.                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Layer 2: RY rotations likewise grouped by corner/edge/center.                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Layer 3: Ring CZ entanglement around the outer cells to propagate correlations.         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Layer 4: Hub-type entanglement using CRZ gates between the center and each edge, with   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ four distinct per-edge parameters to increase expressivity.                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Layer 5: Post-entanglement RZ gates grouped by corner/edge/center.                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ This design increases expressive capacity (78 parameters per block) while preserving      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ symmetry and adjacency constraints, encouraging better generalization and faster          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ convergence. It stays within the given gates and connectivity, and reuses the same        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ parameter-sharing mechanism as the original framework.                                    в”Ӯ
