в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ training setup (data generation, feature map, re-uploading pattern, and training loop).   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ The ANSATZ_SPEC now uses:                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Pre-entanglement RZ rotations with symmetry-based parameter sharing                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - RY rotations with symmetry-based parameter sharing                                      в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Ring entanglement via CRX on the outer ring (shared angle)                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Hub entanglement via CRY from center to edge qubits (shared hub-edge angle)             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Post-entanglement RZ rotations with symmetry-based parameter sharing                    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ This combination aims to improve validation/test performance by leveraging the            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ parameter-efficient CRX/CRY motif while maintaining adjacency constraints and the same    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ parameter budget. The code preserves the original I/O contract and EVOLVE-BLOCK           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ semantics, only changing the ANSATZ_SPEC inside EVOLVE-BLOCK.                             в”Ӯ
