в”Ӯ patch_description        в”Ӯ Proposes a parameter-efficient ANSATZ_SPEC revision for the 9-qubit tic-tac-toe QML task. в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Ring entanglement uses a single shared CRX parameter around the outer perimeter         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ (crx_ring).                                                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Hub entanglement uses two shared parameters across opposite edges: hub_crx for (center, в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 1) and (center, 5); hub_cry for (center, 3) and (center, 7). This enforces symmetry and   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ reduces parameter count.                                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - All other layers preserve the fixed pre/post RZ and RY symmetry-based sharing, ensuring в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ compatibility with the training loop.                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Total parameters per block drop from 13 to 12 (72 total after accounting for 3 uploads  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ and 2 repeats), which should improve generalization and stabilize training while          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ maintaining expressivity.                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Gates remain on allowed adjacent grid edges; the design remains compatible with the     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ existing training pipeline (Adam, etc.).                                                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ This approach aims to improve validation/test performance and reduce overfitting by       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ lowering parameter count and promoting symmetric, bipartisan hub-ring interactions.       в”Ӯ
