в”Ӯ patch_type               в”Ӯ cross                                                                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ patch_name               в”Ӯ hybrid_crx_crz_hub_ansatz                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ patch_description        в”Ӯ This crossover combines the best aspects of three prior implementations:                  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 1. **From the first prior program (score 0.57)**: Uses shared `crz_hub_edge` parameter    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ for all center-to-edge CRZ gates, which reduces parameter count to 60 while maintaining   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ expressiveness through parameter sharing by symmetry.                                     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 2. **From the second prior program (score 0.60)**: Replaces the ring CZ gates with        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ parametrized CRX gates using a shared `crx_ring` parameter. This adds learnable           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ entanglement on the outer ring, which improved validation accuracy to 0.65.               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ 3. **From the current program (score 0.55)**: Uses distinct per-edge hub parameters       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ (`crz_hub_edge_0` through `crz_hub_edge_3`), which provides more flexibility but at the   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ cost of more parameters (78).                                                             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ **Crossover strategy**: Combine the parametrized ring entanglement (CRX with shared       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ parameter) from the second program with the shared hub entanglement (single               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ `crz_hub_edge` parameter) from the first program. This hybrid approach aims to:           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Keep parameter count moderate (around 66-72 parameters)                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Leverage learnable ring entanglement which showed promise (validation accuracy 0.65)    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Maintain parameter efficiency through sharing on the hub layer                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Balance expressiveness with generalization                                              в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ The resulting ansatz has:                                                                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Pre/post RZ rotations with symmetry-based sharing (6 unique parameters)                 в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - RY rotations with symmetry-based sharing (3 unique parameters)                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Parametrized CRX ring with one shared parameter (1 parameter)                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Shared CRZ hub entanglement (1 parameter)                                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ - Total: 11 parameters per block Г— 6 blocks = 66 parameters                               в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ                                                                                           в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ This should improve upon the current score of 0.55 by combining validated improvements    в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ from higher-scoring candidates.                                                           в”Ӯ
